---
// Mock blog / reading view. Exercises fg/bg for body, blue for links, accents
// for headings, and inline code / blockquote / callout patterns.
---

<section class="showcase-section" aria-label="Reading view">
  <header>
    <h2>Reading</h2>
    <p>Long-form body copy, links, code, blockquote, callouts.</p>
  </header>
  <article class="reading" aria-hidden="true">
    <h3>Why OKLCH is the right color space for terminal palettes</h3>
    <p class="meta">
      <span>Dr. Evangelista Colorwheel</span> · <span>8 min read</span> ·
      <a href="#">#colorimetry</a>
    </p>
    <p>
      Working in sRGB hex forces every theme author to eyeball relationships the
      eye actually wants expressed in <strong>perceptual</strong> lightness,
      chroma, and hue. OKLCH gives you those three axes directly — you can step
      through a ramp of eight backgrounds and know they'll <em>feel</em> evenly
      spaced, not just compute evenly.
    </p>
    <blockquote>
      A palette is a contract with your attention. OKLCH makes the contract
      explicit; RGB hides it behind gamma.
    </blockquote>
    <p>
      The CSS spec lets us ship <code>oklch(0.23 0.016 264.1)</code> directly
      and browsers will interpolate correctly in the same space. See <a href="#"
        >CSS Color Module Level 4 § 9.3</a
      > for the gritty bits.
    </p>
    <h4>A small example</h4>
    <pre>
<span class="c-magenta">:root</span> <span class="c-fg">&#123;</span>
  <span class="c-cyan">--accent</span><span class="c-fg">:</span> <span class="c-yellow">oklch(0.62 0.18 280)</span><span class="c-fg">;</span>
  <span class="c-cyan">--accent-hover</span><span class="c-fg">:</span> <span class="c-yellow">oklch(from var(--accent) calc(l + 0.08) c h)</span><span class="c-fg">;</span>
<span class="c-fg">&#125;</span></pre>
    <div class="callout callout-info">
      <strong>Tip:</strong> The <code>from</code> syntax lets you derive hover /
      active variants without touching the hue, which keeps the family coherent
      across both light and dark themes.
    </div>
    <div class="callout callout-warn">
      <strong>Caveat:</strong> <code>oklch(...)</code> lands in Safari Technology
      Preview, Chrome, Firefox, and Edge — but pre-2023 engines fall back to
      transparent. Ship a hex fallback via
      <code>@supports not (color: oklch(0 0 0))</code>.
    </div>
  </article>
</section>

<style>
  .reading {
    padding: 1.4rem 1.6rem 1.6rem;
    border-radius: 0.55rem;
    background: var(--tt-background, oklch(0.98 0.005 260));
    color: var(--tt-foreground, oklch(0.2 0.02 260));
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    max-width: 42rem;
    width: 100%;
    justify-self: center;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 20px color-mix(in oklch, black 14%, transparent);
  }
  .reading h3 {
    margin: 0 0 0.3rem;
    font-size: 1.35rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
    color: var(--tt-foreground);
  }
  .reading h4 {
    margin: 1.35rem 0 0.25rem;
    font-size: 1.02rem;
    color: var(--tt-purple, var(--tt-foreground));
  }
  .reading .meta {
    margin: 0 0 1.2rem;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: color-mix(in oklch, var(--tt-foreground) 60%, transparent);
  }
  .reading a {
    color: var(--tt-blue, var(--tt-foreground));
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-thickness: 1px;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }
  .reading p {
    margin: 0 0 0.85rem;
  }
  .reading strong {
    color: var(--tt-foreground);
    font-weight: 650;
  }
  .reading blockquote {
    margin: 1rem 0;
    padding: 0.45rem 0.95rem;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--tt-purple, var(--tt-blue));
    color: color-mix(in oklch, var(--tt-foreground) 80%, transparent);
    font-style: italic;
  }
  .reading code {
    background: color-mix(in oklch, var(--tt-foreground) 9%, transparent);
    padding: 0.1rem 0.35rem;
    border-radius: 0.25rem;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.85em;
  }
  .reading pre {
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    padding: 0.8rem 1rem;
    border-radius: 0.4rem;
    background: color-mix(in oklch, var(--tt-foreground) 6%, transparent);
    border: 1px solid color-mix(in oklch, var(--tt-foreground) 12%, transparent);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.82em;
    overflow-x: auto;
    white-space: pre;
  }
  .reading pre code {
    background: transparent;
    padding: 0;
  }
  .reading .callout {
    margin: 1rem 0;
    padding: 0.6rem 0.9rem;
    border-left: 3px solid;
    border-radius: 0.3rem;
    background: color-mix(in oklch, var(--tt-foreground) 4%, transparent);
  }
  .reading .callout-info {
    border-color: var(--tt-blue);
  }
  .reading .callout-warn {
    border-color: var(--tt-yellow);
  }

  .reading .c-fg {
    color: var(--tt-foreground);
  }
  .reading .c-magenta {
    color: var(--tt-purple);
  }
  .reading .c-cyan {
    color: var(--tt-cyan);
  }
  .reading .c-yellow {
    color: var(--tt-yellow);
  }
</style>
